section.section:
Of the 15 members:
2 shall be representatives of the physicians and arthritis health professionals at the State's 2 medical schools;
1 shall be a representative of the Department;
1 shall be a representative of the Division of Rehabilitation Services;
1 shall be a representative of the Department of Aging;
1 shall be a representative of the Governor's Committee on Employment of the Handicapped;
3 shall be members of voluntary agencies, including the Maryland Chapter of the Arthritis Foundation, the Maryland Lupus Foundation, and Home Health Care Inc.;
2 shall be representatives from hospitals or health professionals or both outside of the major metropolitan areas;
2 shall be representatives from the health care industry, including the pharmaceutical industry and third-party payors; and
2 shall be arthritic patients or family members of arthritic patients.
